Dialog:--

1. üì¶ What is a Dialog in Jetpack Compose?
    * A Dialog is a small window that prompts the user to make a decision or enter additional information. 
    * It blocks interaction with the rest of the app while it‚Äôs open (modal window).

2. üí° Why Use Dialogs?
   Dialogs are useful for:
   2.1 Confirmations (e.g., logout, delete).
   2.2 Alerts or notifications.
   2.3 User input (e.g., custom forms, name entry).
   2.4 Loading indicators.

3. ‚ú≥Ô∏è Built-in Dialog Types in Jetpack Compose
Jetpack Compose provides multiple dialog options:
  3.1 AlertDialog.
  3.2 Dialog.
  3.3 Dialog(onDismissRequest = {}) ‚Äì for custom content.

4. ‚ú® Properties of AlertDialog:--
| Property           | Description                            |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| `onDismissRequest` | Lambda called when dialog should close |
| `title`            | Composable function for the title      |
| `text`             | Composable function for the content    |
| `confirmButton`    | Main button to confirm action          |
| `dismissButton`    | Optional dismiss button                |
| `shape`, `colors`  | Can be customized inside custom dialog |


5. ‚öôÔ∏è Dialog vs BottomSheet:--
| Feature        | Dialog          | BottomSheet       |
| -------------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| Modal behavior | Blocks screen   | Partially overlay |
| Best for       | Alerts, confirm | Menus, forms      |
| Native Compose | ‚úÖ Yes           | ‚úÖ Yes             |



   

